{
  "info": {
    "name": "Monobase",
    "description": "API collection for the Monobase backend: auth (better-auth), api-gateway (REST + GraphQL proxy), and graphql (NestJS code-first).\n\nArchitecture:\n- gateway ({{gateway_url}}) is the single entry point for browser traffic. It proxies /api/auth/* to the auth service, exposes /api/v1/* REST routes, and forwards POST /graphql/v1 into the graphql service over a Redis/TCP microservice transport.\n- auth ({{auth_url}}) and graphql ({{graphql_url}}) are reachable directly for debugging only.\n\nGraphQL versioning: the GraphQL endpoint is path-versioned to mirror the REST surface — POST /graphql/v1 (gateway) and ws://localhost:3002/graphql/v1 (subscriptions) are the only supported paths.\n\nSession handling: Postman keeps cookies automatically across a session — better-auth sets the session cookie on sign-in and the same cookie is then sent on get-session, admin/* and authed /graphql/v1 calls.\n\nOrigin header: better-auth enforces an Origin check on authenticated state-changing requests. The collection-level pre-request script sets Origin: {{gateway_url}} on every request.\n\nGraphQL admin/users + admin/items: the @repo/graphql service exposes CrudResolvers over the user table (from @repo/db) and the item table. User mutations write directly to Postgres — they bypass better-auth password hashing and account-row creation, so users created via createOneUser cannot sign in via email/password until a password is set through the auth API.\n\nItem file upload: each item can have multiple files attached via the polymorphic uploaded_file table. Uploads are multipart REST requests handled directly by the graphql service (NOT proxied by the gateway): POST {{graphql_url}}/api/v1/items/:itemId/files. The server stores the binary in MinIO, generates thumbnails for compressible images, and returns presigned GET URLs in the response. The Item GraphQL type exposes a `files` field for read access.\n\nSubscriptions: createdUser / updatedOneUser / deletedOneUser (and the createdItem/updatedOneItem/deletedOneItem variants) are GraphQL subscriptions and require WebSocket transport. Use a Postman WebSocket request to ws://localhost:3002/graphql/v1 to test them — they aren't included as collection items because Postman models WS separately.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// better-auth requires Origin header on authenticated state-changing requests",
          "// (CSRF protection). Always send the gateway URL as Origin.",
          "const gatewayUrl = pm.collectionVariables.get('gateway_url');",
          "if (gatewayUrl) {",
          "  pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'Origin', value: gatewayUrl });",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
