    {
      "name": "Item Files (multipart upload)",
      "description": "Multi-file upload scoped to a specific item. Endpoints live on the graphql service (NOT proxied by the gateway), so requests target {{graphql_url}} directly.\n\nFlow:\n1. Create an item via 'GraphQL — Admin Items (CRUD) → Create One Item' to populate {{created_item_id}}.\n2. POST one or more files to {{graphql_url}}/api/v1/items/:itemId/files with multipart form-data (field name 'files', up to 10 files per call). The server stores binaries in MinIO, generates JPEG thumbnails for compressible images (jpeg/png/webp/tiff/bmp), and stamps each row with entityType='item', entityId=:itemId.\n3. Read back via REST (List Files for Item) or via GraphQL (the `files` field on Item).\n\nResponse shape per file: { id, filename, originalFilename, mimetype, size, url, thumbnailUrl?, hasThumbnail, entityType, entityId, uploadedById?, createdAt }. `url` and `thumbnailUrl` are presigned MinIO GETs that expire after 2 hours.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Upload Files for Item",
          "description": "Multipart POST. In Postman: Body → form-data → key='files', type='File', then attach one or more files. The endpoint accepts up to 10 files per request via FilesInterceptor('files', 10).\n\nThe collection-level Origin header doesn't apply here (better-auth isn't on this path), but it doesn't hurt to send it. Test script captures the first uploaded file's id into {{uploaded_file_id}}.",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (Array.isArray(json) && json.length > 0 && json[0].id) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('uploaded_file_id', json[0].id);",
                  "  console.log('Saved uploaded_file_id:', json[0].id);",
                  "} else {",
                  "  console.log('Unexpected response:', JSON.stringify(json));",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "files",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": [],
                  "description": "Repeat this 'files' key for each additional file (up to 10)."
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{graphql_url}}/api/v1/items/{{created_item_id}}/files",
              "host": ["{{graphql_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "items", "{{created_item_id}}", "files"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List Files for Item",
          "description": "GET every uploaded_file row scoped to (entityType='item', entityId=:itemId). Each entry includes a fresh presigned URL (and thumbnailUrl when applicable).",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{graphql_url}}/api/v1/items/{{created_item_id}}/files",
              "host": ["{{graphql_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "items", "{{created_item_id}}", "files"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete All Files for Item",
          "description": "Bulk delete every file attached to the item — removes the MinIO objects (including thumbnails) and the DB rows. Returns 204 No Content.",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{graphql_url}}/api/v1/items/{{created_item_id}}/files",
              "host": ["{{graphql_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "items", "{{created_item_id}}", "files"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete Uploaded File",
          "description": "Delete a single uploaded_file row by id (across any entity). Uses {{uploaded_file_id}} captured by Upload Files for Item.",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{graphql_url}}/api/v1/uploaded-files/{{uploaded_file_id}}",
              "host": ["{{graphql_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "uploaded-files", "{{uploaded_file_id}}"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
